The paper discusses the topic of robust machine learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The specific focus is on black-box adversarial attacks, which are commonly studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The paper also mentions the use of optimization techniques, which are relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and cryptography (cs.CR) subfields. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed methods on image classification datasets, which is a common task in the neural networks (cs.NE) subfield.
